  "question": "What are the major products and services that AMD sells as of FY22?",
  "answer": "Based on the provided document chunks, as of FY22, AMD's major products and services include:\n\n*   **Data Center Products**: Server CPUs (AMD EPYC™), GPUs (AMD Instinct™, Radeon™ PRO V), DPUs (AMD Pensando), FPGAs, and Adaptive SoCs (including Zynq™, Versal™, Virtex™, and Kintex™) [PAGE 7].\n*   **Client Products**: Desktop and notebook CPUs (AMD Ryzen™, AMD Athlon™), APUs that integrate CPUs and GPUs, chipsets, and discrete GPUs (AMD Radeon™ RX series) [PAGE 7][PAGE 9].\n*   **Embedded Products**: Embedded CPUs, GPUs, APUs, FPGAs, and Adaptive SoC products [PAGE 4][PAGE 9].\n*   **Gaming and Professional Products**: Semi-custom SoC products and development services, and professional GPUs (AMD Radeon™ PRO) [PAGE 4][PAGE 9][PAGE 12].\n*   **Services**: Microprocessor and SoC development services and technology [PAGE 60]. The company may also sell or license portions of its intellectual property (IP) portfolio [PAGE 4][PAGE 60].",
